The paper discusses building a semantic search engine for scientific articles, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. This aligns with several sub-categories in computer science, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Deep Learning (cs.DL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on text analysis and classification, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories.
